command_no_permission: &cJe hebt geen toestemming om dit commando te gebruiken.
error_version: Deze plugin is niet compatibel met Minecraft versies onder 1.13.
error_version_spigot: Deze plugin is niet compatibel met Spigot 1.13!
format_cancel_confirm: %s Geannuleerde taken kunnen niet worden voortgezet. Als u zeker weet dat u wilt annuleren, typ '/chunky confirm'.
format_continue_no_tasks: %s Geen taken om mee door te gaan.
format_delete_confirm: %s &cWarning: Chunks in %s outside of the %s region centered at %d, %d with radius %s will be permanently deleted. Please make sure you have taken a backup of your server before continuing to avoid potential damage. You will be required to restart your server fully after the task has finished. If you understand and wish to proceed, type '/chunky confirm'.
format_radii: %s Radius changed for x to %d, and for z to %d.
format_reload_tasks_running: %s The configuration cannot be reloaded while tasks are running.
format_start: %s Taak begonnen voor %s om %d, %d met de radius %s.
format_start_confirm: %s A task was already started for this world. To continue running it, type '/chunky continue'. To start a new task, type '/chunky confirm'.
format_start_disk: %s The server only has %s disk space remaining, but the estimated disk space required for the task is %s. If you wish to start anyway, type '/chunky confirm'.
help_cancel: &2chunky cancel&r - Stop and delete current or saved tasks
help_center: &2chunky center <x> <z>&r - Set the center block location
help_continue: &2chunky continue&r - Continue current or saved tasks
help_pattern: &bchunky patroon <pattern>&r - Stel het generatie patroon in
help_pause: &2chunky pause&r - Pause current tasks and save progress
help_shape: &2chunky shape <shape>&r - Stel de vorm in om te genereren
help_silent: &2chunky stil&r - Schakel tussen het tonen van update berichten
help_spawn: &2chunky spawn&r - Set the center to the spawn point
help_start: &2chunky start&r - Start a new chunk generation task
help_worldborder: &2chunky worldborder&r - Use the world border center & radius
task_done: %s Task finished for %s. Processed: %d chunks (%.2f%%), Total time: %01d:%02d:%02d
task_update: %s Task running for %s. Processed: %d chunks (%.2f%%), ETA: %01d:%02d:%02d, Rate: %.1f cps, Current: %d, %d
